<font color="#FF0000">EFFECTS OF PROTESTORS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Mar 25 10:48:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
 Howdy!My name is Julia and I am a student at Texas A&amp;M University in College Station.  I have been browsing this site off and on for the last couple weeks. Some of the entries have been absolutely heart-wrenching while others have been much more subdued.  Yet, regardless of the nature of the entries, they have all given me a lot to contemplate.<br>
 The reason I am writing is because I am doing a historical essay on the effects the protests in America had on Vietnam veterans returning home.  Because it is a historical paper I am limited to primary sources.  Of course, there was very little information printed concerning this topic throughout the duration of the war.  Therefore, I must depend upon personal accounts for most of my information.  I am having trouble finding specific information and am hoping I will receive some responses.<br>
 Any information you could give would be greatly appreciated.  Memories, incidents, emotions, interactions, etc. would be wonderful.  You can either e-mail them to me if you don't want them posted here or simply respond through this website.  I thank you profusely for your time and effort in responding.<br>
 PS-If anyone is aware of any websights involving some aspect of this topic, PLEASE tell!<br><br>
Julia<br>
 
